\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces RSI comparison across all six APEX conditions, ordered by descending mean survival index. Error bars represent $\pm $1 seed standard deviation. The three-tier structure --- augmentation conditions (C24, CAB) above 0.45, transition conditions (AFC, PAR) between 0.21 and 0.29, and replacement conditions (HAO, FAR) below 0.15 --- constitutes the primary structural finding of the APEX evaluation.}}{7}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rsi_comparison_across_all_six_}{{1}{7}{RSI comparison across all six APEX conditions, ordered by descending mean survival index. Error bars represent $\pm $1 seed standard deviation. The three-tier structure --- augmentation conditions (C24, CAB) above 0.45, transition conditions (AFC, PAR) between 0.21 and 0.29, and replacement conditions (HAO, FAR) below 0.15 --- constitutes the primary structural finding of the APEX evaluation}{figure.1}{}}
