\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Seed sensitivity (RSI standard deviation across seeds 0, 1, 2) per condition. The Conservative 2024 Baseline (C24) exhibits the highest seed variance, reflecting residual macroeconomic volatility in near-term augmentation scenarios. All replacement-regime conditions converge toward near-zero seed variance as parametric displacement terms dominate the RSI computation.}}{8}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:seed_sensitivity_rsi_standard_}{{2}{8}{Seed sensitivity (RSI standard deviation across seeds 0, 1, 2) per condition. The Conservative 2024 Baseline (C24) exhibits the highest seed variance, reflecting residual macroeconomic volatility in near-term augmentation scenarios. All replacement-regime conditions converge toward near-zero seed variance as parametric displacement terms dominate the RSI computation}{figure.2}{}}
